  "instructions": [
    "In a large bowl, whisk together hojicha powder, oat flour, buckwheat flour, and salt.",
    "Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients and pour in almond milk, coconut yogurt, and yuzu juice.",
    "Whisk the mixture until it's smooth and free of lumps.",
    "Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat and brush with coconut oil.",
    "Using a 1/4 cup measuring cup, scoop the batter onto the skillet or griddle.",
    "Cook for 2-3 minutes, until the edges start to set and the surface is dry.",
    "Flip the pancakes and cook for another 1-2 minutes, until golden brown.",
    "Serve the pancakes warm with a sprinkle of yuzu-cure and a pinch of salt."
